Health Minister Zweli Mkhize was speaking at the release of the UNDP's Socio-Economic Impact Assessment of COVID-19 on South Africa. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says South Africa is moving away from the peak of the COVID-19 pandemic. Mkhize says the recovery rate continues to increase and that is a positive sign. He was speaking at the release of the UNDP's Socio-Economic Impact Assessment of COVID-19 on South Africa. READ: Second COVID-19 vaccine trial begins in SA South Africa has 592,144 confirmed COVID-19 cases. The recoveries stand at 485,468 translating to a recovery rate of 82 percent. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.